Referring to Secundus's last remarks, Maternus shows from them that eloquence is the child of discord, turbulence, and violence, that its existence is consequently an index of unsettled political conditions and defective government. Why, therefore, should we deplore its deca- dence? Let us enjoy the advantages of our own. time, and not regret the lack of what we do not need.
